Issues.Body:
### .NET version

.NET 10.0 SDK build: 10.0.100-preview.2.25112.51

### Did it work in .NET Framework?

Yes

### Did it work in any of the earlier releases of .NET Core or .NET 5+?

Yes, work in .NET 8.0, repro in .NET 9.0 and 10.0

### Issue description

The icon of errorProvider is not scaled well on HDPI screen with SystemAware and PerMoniterV2 modes

**.NET 10.0 on 300%DPI:**

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d341907a-f84d-483c-81dc-ace6d77943ad)

**.NET 8.0 on 300%DPI:**

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a6250773-8dd8-40cc-af61-64dfb91bc0f5)

### Steps to reproduce

1. Create a Winforms .NET application with TextBox and ErrorProvider controls added
2. Double-click TextBox control to generate **textBox1_TextChanged** event
3. In that event, write some code to show errorProvider for TextBox editing
 ```
private void textBox1_TextChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
 {
     if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(textBox1.Text))
     {
         errorProvider1.SetError(textBox1, "ErrorProvider shown");
     }
     else
     {
         errorProvider1.SetError(textBox1, string.Empty);
     }
 }
```
or using following sample app
